body:
Tom Holland and Secrets

I think one of the reasons why Tom Holland is bad at keeping secrers is because of the fact that he’s a Gemini sun. Before ya’ll come at me, I know other factors should come into play but I don’t mean this in a malicious, calling Geminis snitches sort of way. It’s that, from my observation, Gemini suns and air suns in general are pretty talkative. They tend to give tmi without meaning to, sometimes they’re not even aware that you want them to keep something a secret. Even their own personal secrets they tend to spill without meaning to. Just ask them all the right questions and bam, all the answers spilt. I find this happens most especially when Geminis are passionate about something. And we all know that Tom Holland is really passionate about his work with the MCU and because of this and his excitement tends to unwittingly overshare details. Sometimes he’s not even aware he’s done it until someone points it out for him. Thoughts? 😁

summary: One thing I will forever love about Steve’s dynamic with the twins: when they turned to start helping the Avengers, he didn’t...
body:
One thing I will forever love about Steve’s dynamic with the twins: when they turned to start helping the Avengers, he didn’t question them. He didn’t stop and yell at them for what they had done.

(I mean he was forced to remember Peggy and the entire life he lost).

He didn’t get angry with them. Sure he had a moment of “I’m very tempted not to give you one” when Pietro needed a breather after saving all the civilians, but beyond that he never questioned or doubted them.

This becomes obvious when the twins go back to the compound with him and they’re insulted constantly and Clint shoots the ground beneath Pietro.

Steve was the only Avenger that didn’t stop for a second as soon as he saw them helping and honestly talked to them as though they had been on the same side all along. He used their powers to help as though they were already Avengers and trusted Wanda when she warned him that Tony may try to create another Ultron.

While I don’t blame the other Avengers for being upset, I absolutely adore the fact that Steve saw they were willing to help and basically forgave and accepted them immediately.

When everyone else held the mindset of them always being villains, he was the one that understood them and accepted them into the Avengers.

So, yes Clint was a close friend to the Maximoffs, but Steve was always there for them from the start.
